data.chText: 物体；物品；东西
data.enText: a thing that can be seen and touched, but is not alive

data.chText: 诸如杯碟之类的日用品
data.enText: everyday objects such as cups and saucers

data.chText: 架子上排列着玻璃和塑料制品。
data.enText: Glass and plastic objects lined the shelves.

data.chText: （极欲得到、研究、注意等的）对象
data.enText: a person or thing that sb desires , studies, pays attention to, etc.

data.chText: 宗旨；目的；目标
data.enText: an aim or a purpose

data.chText: 她人生的唯一目标就是当游记作家。
data.enText: Her sole object in life is to become a travel writer.

data.chText: 目的就是教育人们注意交通安全。
data.enText: The object is to educate people about road safety.

data.chText: 如果你迟到了，便不能达到整个活动的目的。
data.enText: If you're late, you'll defeat the whole object of the exercise .

data.chText: 宾语（包括直接宾语、间接宾语）
data.enText: a noun, noun phrase or pronoun that refers to a person or thing that is affected by the action of the verb (called the direct object ), or that the action is done to or for (called the indirect object )
expense, money, etc. is no object

data.chText: 费用不在话下；钱不成问题
data.enText: used to say that you are willing to spend a lot of money

data.chText: 他总是乘头等舱旅行，从不计较花费多少。
data.enText: He always travels first class─expense is no object.

data.chText: 不同意；不赞成；反对
data.enText: to say that you disagree with, disapprove of or oppose sth

data.chText: 许多当地的居民反对兴建新机场。
data.enText: Many local people object to the building of the new airport.

data.chText: 如果没有人反对，我们就把会议推迟到下周。
data.enText: If nobody objects, we'll postpone the meeting till next week.

data.chText: 我非常反对收停车费。
data.enText: I really object to being charged for parking.

data.chText: 提出…作为反对的理由；抗辩说
data.enText: to give sth as a reason for opposing sth

data.chText: 他抗辩说警察没有充分的证据就逮捕了他。
data.enText: He objected that the police had arrested him without sufficient evidence.

data.text: complain ♦ protest ♦ object ♦ grumble ♦ moan ♦ whine ♦ whinge

data.chText: 以上各词均含对人或事物感到恼怒、不高兴或不满之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to say that you are annoyed, unhappy or not satisfied about sb/sth.
complain

data.chText: 指抱怨、埋怨、发牢骚：
data.enText: to say that you are annoyed, unhappy or not satisfied about sb/sth

data.chText: 我要就这件事给经理提意见。
data.enText: I'm going to complain to the manager about this.
protest

data.chText: 指公开反对、抗议或申辩：
data.enText: to say or do sth to show that you disagree with or disapprove of sth, especially publicly; to give sth as a reason for protesting

data.chText: 学生走上街头抗议这项决定。
data.enText: Students took to the streets to protest against the decision.
object

data.chText: 指不同意、不赞成、反对或抗辩：
data.enText: to say that you disagree with or disapprove of sth; to give sth as a reason for objecting

data.chText: 如果没有人反对，我们就把会议推迟到下周。
data.enText: If nobody objects, we'll postpone the meeting till next week.

data.chText: 他抗辩说警察没有充分证据就逮捕了他。
data.enText: He objected that the police had arrested him without sufficient evidence.
grumble

data.chText: 指咕哝、嘟囔、发牢骚：
data.enText: ( rather informal , disapproving ) to complain about sb/sth in a bad-tempered way

data.chText: 他们不停地嘟囔着说冷。
data.enText: They kept grumbling that they were cold.
moan

data.chText: 指抱怨、埋怨：
data.enText: ( BrE , rather informal , disapproving ) to complain about sb/sth in an annoying way

data.chText: 你在抱怨什么呢？
data.enText: What are you moaning on about now?
whine

data.chText: 指哭哭啼啼或哭嚷着诉说：
data.enText: ( rather informal , disapproving ) to complain in an annoying, crying voice

data.chText: 别哭哭啼啼的！
data.enText: Stop whining!

data.chText: “我要回家。”托比哼哼唧唧地说。
data.enText: ‘I want to go home,’ whined Toby.

data.chText: whine通常用于小孩子抱怨。
data.enText: Whine is often used to talk about the way that young children complain.
whinge

data.chText: 指絮絮叨叨地抱怨：
data.enText: ( BrE , informal , disapproving ) to complain about sb/sth in an annoying way

data.chText: 她总是嘟囔着说一切都太不公平了。
data.enText: She's always whingeing about how unfair everything is.

data.chText: 用grumble、moan还是whinge？
以上三词均为complain的非正式用词。grumble表达抱怨者的感受，即心情不好；moan和whinge多表达听者的心情，即抱怨使人心烦。
data.enText: These are all fairly informal words for ‘complain’. Grumble tells you how the person who is complaining feels (= they are in a bad mood) ; moan and whinge tell you more about how the people listening to the complaints feel (= the complaining is annoying them) .
grumble, moan or whinge ?
to complain/protest/grumble/moan/whine/whinge about sth
to complain/protest/grumble/moan at sth
to complain/protest/object/grumble/moan/whine/whinge to sb
to complain/protest/object/grumble/moan/whine that…
to complain/protest/object bitterly

data.chText: 以上各词均指目标、目的。
data.enText: These are all words for sth that you are trying to achieve.
target

data.chText: 指试图达到的目标、指标：
data.enText: a result that you try to achieve

data.chText: 给自己制订有望达到的指标。
data.enText: Set yourself targets that you can reasonably hope to achieve.

data.chText: 学校的成绩目标
data.enText: attainment targets in schools
objective

data.chText: 指正努力达到的目标、目的：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) something that you are trying to achieve

data.chText: 这个项目的主要目标是什么？
data.enText: What is the main objective of this project?
goal

data.chText: 指希望达到的目标、目的：
data.enText: something that you hope to achieve

data.chText: 他继续追求他成为演员的目标。
data.enText: He continued to pursue his goal of becoming an actor.

data.chText: 用targett﹑objective还是goal？
target通常为以某种方式正式记录的指标，如由雇主或政府委员会等制订，常为具体的数字，如销售量、考试及格率、日期等；objective通常指为自己制订的、希望达到的目标，常为某一项目或发言的一部分；goal通常指长远目标，与人生和职业规划、公司或机构的长远规划有关。
data.enText: A target is usually officially recorded in some way, for example by an employer or by a government committee. It is often specific, and in the form of figures, such as number of sales or examination passes, or a date. People often set their own objectives : these are things that they wish to achieve, often as part of a project or a talk they are giving. Goals are often long-term, and relate to people's life and career plans or the long-term plans of a company or organization.
target, objective or goal?
object

data.chText: 指目的、目标、宗旨：
data.enText: the purpose of sth; sth that you plan to achieve

data.chText: 目的就是教育大众注意交通安全。
data.enText: The object is to educate people about road safety.
end

data.chText: 指计划达到的目的、目标：
data.enText: something that you plan to achieve

data.chText: 他为了政治目的加入了这个协会。
data.enText: He joined the society for political ends.

data.chText: 除非你认为只要目的正确可以不择手段，不然那是不可以接受的。
data.enText: That's only OK if you believe that the end justifies the means (= bad methods of doing sth are acceptable if the final result is good) .

data.chText: end通常以复数形式或在某些固定短语中出现。
data.enText: End usually occurs in the plural or in particular fixed expressions.
to work towards a(n) target/objective/goal
a(n) impossible/ambitious/difficult/tough/unrealistic target/objective/goal
economic/financial/business/sales targets/objectives/goals
to set/reach/succeed in/meet/exceed/fall short of/agree/identify a(n) target/objective/goal
to achieve a(n) target/objective/goal/end
attainment/recruitment targets

data.text: objects you can use可以使用的物体

data.chText: 有些一般性词汇可用于描述物体，尤其是不知道名称的东西。
data.enText: It is useful to know some general words to help you describe objects, especially if you do not know the name of a particular object.

data.chText: device指为特定用途设计的装置、器具、器械：
data.enText: A device is something that has been designed to do a particular job.

data.chText: 有一种新的汽车装置可提醒司机前面有交通堵塞。
data.enText: There is a new device for cars that warns drivers of traffic jams ahead.

data.chText: gadget指有用、但不一定必需的小器具、小装置：
data.enText: A gadget is a small object that does something useful, but is not really necessary.

data.chText: 他厨房里到处是他从不使用的小器具。
data.enText: His kitchen is full of gadgets he never uses.

data.chText: instrument尤指做精密或科学工作的仪器、器械、器具：
data.enText: An instrument is used especially for delicate or scientific work.

data.chText: “测量温度的仪器叫什么？”“温度计。”
data.enText: ‘What do you call the instrument that measures temperature?’ ‘A thermometer.’

data.chText: tool指制造或修理用的工具、用具：
data.enText: A tool is something that you use for making and repairing things.

data.chText: “你有拧螺丝钉的工具吗？”“你是指螺丝刀吗？”
data.enText: ‘Have you got one of those tools for turning screws?’ ‘Do you mean a screwdriver?’

data.chText: machine指有特定用途的机器，通常为独立设备：
data.enText: A machine has moving parts and is used for a particular job. It usually stands on its own.

data.chText: “搅拌器是什么？”“搅和软食物或液汁的电动机器。”
data.enText: ‘What’s a blender?’ ‘It’s an electric machine for mixing soft food or liquid.’

data.chText: appliance指大型家用机器，如洗衣机。
data.enText: An appliance is a large machine that you use in the house, such as a washing machine.

data.chText: equipment统称某项活动所需的设备、装备：
data.enText: Equipment means all the things you need for a particular activity.

data.chText: 攀登用装备
data.enText: climbing equipment

data.chText: apparatus统称做某事所用的设备、用具、器械、装置：
data.enText: Apparatus means all the tools, machines or equipment that you need for something.

data.chText: 戴着呼吸装置的消防人员
data.enText: firefighters wearing breathing apparatus

simple_means.memory_skill: ob 反对 + ject 扔 → 逆着〔某物〕扔〔东西〕→ 反对

means: (极欲得到、研究、注意等的)对象

ex.chText: 如果没人反对的话，该计划将立即执行。
ex.enText: If no one objects, the plan will be implemented immediately.

ex.chText: 她坚决反对重建该寺庙。
ex.enText: She strongly objected to rebuilding the temple.

ex.chText: 她不赞成聘用那个男人。
ex.enText: She objected to recruiting that man.

synonyms.bx: 语气强烈，指对某一具体做法、计划等表示反对，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 我不反对你的计划。
ex.enText: I have no objection to your plan.

tips.tip: 在表示“不反对…”时，习惯上用 have no objection to，而不用 do not object to。

ex.chText: 经济学家对通货膨胀的原因看法不一。
ex.enText: Economists differ on the cause of inflation.

ex.chText: 他总是与她意见相左。
ex.enText: He always differs with her.

ex.chText: 在这件事上我和你意见不同。
ex.enText: I disagree with you on this matter.

ex.chText: 即便是亲密的朋友有时也有分歧。
ex.enText: Even close friends disagree sometimes.

ex.chText: 有些人不同意他的论点。
ex.enText: Some people disagree with his argument.

synonyms.bx: 指与他人在看法上有分歧，也指不赞同计划、行动等，语气较differ 强烈，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 国会会继续反对总统的经济紧缩措施吗？
ex.enText: Will the Congress continue to oppose the President's austerity measures?

ex.chText: 委员会反对改变规则。
ex.enText: The committee opposed changing the regulations.

ex.chText: 当地居民强烈反对这个计划。
ex.enText: The local residents bitterly opposed the scheme.

ex.chText: 我们反对任何外来势力插手干预。
ex.enText: We oppose interference by any outside force.

synonyms.bx: 指不赞同某一政策、计划等，含抵制或阻挠之意。

ex.chText: 成千上万的人走上街头，抗议经济紧缩政策。
ex.enText: Tens of thousands of people took to the streets, protesting against the austerity policy.

ex.chText: 许多学生反对那项决定。
ex.enText: Many students protested the decision.

ex.chText: 数千人抗议新法规。
ex.enText: Thousands of people protested against the new legislation.

ex.chText: “我不明白为什么他会升职！”她抗议道。
ex.enText: 'I don't see why he should get the promotion!' she protested.

synonyms.bx: 通常指人们聚集在一起，以言语、行为等公开表示不满或异议，也可指个人不认同某事或对某事心有不满。

ex.chText: 那位部长顶住了要求其辞职的压力。
ex.enText: The minister resisted pressure to resign.

ex.chText: 为什么该计划遭到董事会的强烈反对？
ex.enText: Why was the plan fiercely resisted by the board?

ex.chText: 该公司拒绝改变聘用制度。
ex.enText: The company resisted changing its recruitment system.

synonyms.bx: 指拒绝作出改变或不屈从于外力而做某事。

ex.chText: 他来纽约是为了做生意。
ex.enText: He came to New York with the purpose of doing business.

ex.chText: 这次会议的目的是讨论如何应对此次危机。
ex.enText: The purpose of this meeting is to discuss how to deal with the crisis.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指经过考虑而要做某事的意图，通常用单数。

ex.chText: 这一课程的主要目标是提高口语。
ex.enText: The main aim of this course is to improve your oral English.

ex.chText: 旨在帮助罪案受害者的运动已经在全球范围内得到了关注。
ex.enText: The campaign with the aim of helping the victims of crime has received worldwide attention.

synonyms.bx: 强调希望做成某事的具体意图，多指短期目标。

ex.chText: 你的最终目标是什么？
ex.enText: What is your ultimate goal?

ex.chText: 他们实现扩大公司市场份额的目标了吗？
ex.enText: Did they reach their goal of expanding the company's market share?

synonyms.bx: 多指想要通过一段时间的努力而在未来实现某事的意图。

ex.chText: 家长们首先想知道这项游戏的目的是什么。
ex.enText: The parents first wanted to know what the object of this game was.

ex.chText: 低收入人群将获益最大，这正是此举的目的。
ex.enText: People with low income will benefit the most, and that is the object of this exercise.

synonyms.bx: 指某一计划、行为或活动的目的，通常用单数。

ex.chText: 你应该在下学期开始的时候制定一个目标。
ex.enText: You should set an objective at the beginning of next semester.

ex.chText: 他在总统任期结束之前必须实现某些目标。
ex.enText: He has to achieve certain objectives before the end of his presidency.

synonyms.bx: 尤用于商业或政治方面，侧重指人所想要实现的目标。

ex.chText: 财务指标
ex.enText: financial targets

ex.chText: 新大楼完工的预定日期是什么时候？
ex.enText: What is the target date for completion of the new building?

synonyms.bx: 多用于数量、时间、财务等方面，表示想要达到的具体目标。

data.enText: expense, money, etc. is no object

data.chText: 费用不在话下；钱不成问题
data.enText: used to say that you are willing to spend a lot of money

data.chText: 他总是乘头等舱旅行，从不计较花费多少。
data.enText: He always travels first class─expense is no object.

tr: an entity that can cast a shadow
example: it was full of rackets, balls and other objects

tr: the focus of cognitions or feelings
the goal intended to be attained (and which is believed to be attainable)
example: the sole object of her trip was to see her children

tr: (computing) a discrete item that provides a description of virtually anything known to a computer
example: in object-oriented programming, objects include data and define its status, its methods of operation and how it interacts with other objects

tr: (grammar) a constituent that is acted upon
express or raise an objection or protest or criticism or express dissent
example: She never objected to the amount of work her boss charged her with
When asked to drive the truck, she objected that she did not have a driver's license

tr: be averse to or express disapproval of
example: My wife objects to modern furniture

value.boxr_value: The noun is pronounced /'ɒbdʒɪkt/. The verb is pronounced /əb'dʒekt/. 名词读作/'ɒbdʒɪkt/。动词读作/əb'dʒekt/。

value.def: An object is anything that has a fixed shape or form, that you can touch or see, and that is not alive.

example.ex: He squinted his eyes as though he were studying an object on the horizon.
example.tran: 他眯起眼睛，就好像在端详地平线上的某一物体。

example.ex: ...an object the shape of a coconut...
In the cosy consulting room the children are surrounded by familiar objects.
example.tran: 在温馨的诊疗室里，孩子们周围摆满了亲切熟悉的东西。

value.def: The object of what someone is doing is their aim or purpose.

example.ex: The object of the exercise is to raise money for the charity...
He made it his object in life to find the island...
example.tran: 他把找到那座岛屿当成自己的人生目标。

example.ex: My object was to publish a scholarly work on Peter Mourne.
example.tran: 我的目标是出版一本关于彼得·莫恩的学术著作。

value.def: The object of a particular feeling or reaction is the person or thing it is directed towards or that causes it.

example.ex: The object of her hatred was 24-year-old model Ros French...
example.tran: 令她心头生恨的是24岁的模特罗斯·弗伦奇。

example.ex: The object of great interest at the Temple was a large marble tower built in memory of Buddha...
example.tran: 这处庙宇最引人注目的是一座为纪念佛陀而修建的宏伟的大理石塔。

example.ex: She knew that she was an object of pity among her friends.
example.tran: 她知道自己是朋友们同情的对象。

value.def: In grammar, the object of a verb or a preposition is the word or phrase which completes the structure begun by the verb or preposition.
If you object to something, you express your dislike or disapproval of it.

example.ex: A lot of people will object to the book...
example.tran: 很多人都会对这本书表示反感。

example.ex: Cullen objected that his small staff would be unable to handle the added work...
example.tran: 卡伦提出反对，说他的人手较少，无法完成额外工作。

example.ex: We objected strongly but were outvoted...
example.tran: 我们强烈表示反对，但还是被否决了。

example.ex: 'Hey, I don't know what you're talking about,' Russo objected.
example.tran: “喂，我不知道你在说些什么，”拉索反驳道。

value.def: If you say that money is no object or distance is no object, you are emphasizing that you are willing or able to spend as much money as necessary or travel whatever distance is required.

example.ex: Hugh Johnson's shop in London has a range of superb Swedish crystal glasses that I would have if money were no object...
example.tran: 休·约翰逊伦敦店出售各种美轮美奂的瑞典水晶玻璃杯，不考虑钱的话我都想买。

example.ex: Although he was based in Wales, distance was no object.
example.tran: 虽然他主要住在威尔士，但是距离不成问题。

value.tran: 钱不成问题/距离不在话下
